{"data":{"markdownRemark":null,"npmPackage":{"name":"gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice","description":"Gatsby plugin to get yodorada webservice rest api data.","keywords":["gatsby","gatsby-plugin","gatsby-source-plugin"],"lastPublisher":{"name":"yodorada","avatar":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/3e44374d7b78187b783b25044aa57d0f"},"repository":null,"readme":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice\"><a href=\"#gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice</h1>\n<p>Gatsby source plugin to get Yodorada RESTful API data, see: <a href=\"https://github.com/yodorada/PHP-Webservice-REST-API\">PHP-Webservice-REST-API</a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"install\"><a href=\"#install\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm install --save gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice</code></p>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-use\"><a href=\"#how-to-use\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to use</h2>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"javascript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token comment\">// In your gatsby-config.js</span>\nplugins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    resolve<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      host<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`https://www.hostname.com/api/`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the absolute path to your RESTful API</span>\n      user<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`YOUR_USERNAME`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the login username </span>\n      password<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`YOUR_PASSWORD`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the login password </span>\n      apiKey<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`YOUR_APIKEY`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the unique api key </span>\n      endpoints<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`authors`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`aphorisms`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// the endpoints from where you want to fetch</span>\n      conflictPrefix<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`yo_`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// rename conflicting fields, will be camelCased (eg: yoId)</span>\n      options<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// additional options (not yet implemented)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2 id=\"how-to-query\"><a href=\"#how-to-query\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>How to query</h2>\n<p>Data will be available at the following points in GraphQL.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">allYodoradaEndpoint</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">yodoradaEndpoint</code> where <code class=\"language-text\">Endpoint</code> is replaced by the respective endpoint name in the configuration options.</p>\n<p>An example: Get all entries from authors database:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"graphql\">\n      <pre class=\"language-graphql\"><code class=\"language-graphql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">query</span> Authors <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  allYodoradaAuthors<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token attr-name\">sort</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token attr-name\">fields</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>authorname<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">order</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> DESC<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    edges <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      node <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        id\n        yoId\n        authorname\n        created\n        changed\n      <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>","timeToRead":1}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/packages/gatsby-source-yodorada-webservice/","id":"155ed327-65b2-530d-be10-9a69bd6778a2"}}